cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language generation and summarization, which are core topics in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses neural networks (cs.LG) and abstract meaning representation (AMR), which is a semantic representation of natural language (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach using ROUGE, a metric commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
